  "text": "Our AFLP methodology was essentially as described in [CITATION_1] , with the following modifications. For each leaf sample, we digested and ligated approximately 200 ng of genomic DNA using the AFLP Core Reagent Kit (Life Technologies). We added 1.4 ml of a 1 mg/ml solution of RNAse in each 25 ml restriction digest reaction to remove the large amount of RNA present in G. caleyi DNA extracts. We confirmed complete digestion of genomic DNA by visualisation on an agarose gel. We carried out all PCR reactions in 0.2 ml PCR tubes using a PTC-100 thermal cycler (MJ Research). The touchdown reaction for selective PCR amplification commenced with one cycle of 941C for 30 s, 651C for 30 s and 721C for 60 s, followed by reduction of the annealing temperature in each cycle by 11C from 65 to 561C. We maintained the annealing temperature at 561C for 23 cycles.",
